The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Indian colts beat Spain

New Delhi: India rallied to beat Spain 3-2 for their second straight win at the four-nation junior hockey meet in Bilbao. 

Holland recorded a 5-1 thumping of Chile, according to information received here. 

Spain took the lead in the first half but as soon as the game resumed India scored two quick goals through drag flicker Sandeep Singh. 

They consolidated their position further when V. Raja scored in the 58th minute, converting a pass from Tushar Khandekar into the net. 

Though the Spaniards reduced the margin, India preserved their lead to emerge winners. India, who play Chile in their last match, just need a draw to win the title. (PTI) 




